{
  "texts": [
    "Multilingual communication interfacesApplications in global settings that are often lower-resourced would likely require non-English interaction.",
    "As current evaluation benchmarks, including our novel adversarial benchmark, are typically monolingual English datasets, supporting multilingual evaluations is an important step forward for assessments whose results are more likely to generalize to global settings.",
    "A less straightforward challenge remains that open-source medical LLMs are typically pretrained on biomedical data primarily written in English [47], which may limit the transfer capabilities of their learned knowledge in non-English interactions.",
    "Future research should expand MEDITRON (and other medical LLMs) to multilingual settings by developing non-English communication interfaces that can transfer knowledge learned by training on English-skewed domain data.",
    "The release of our models, code, and datasets represents an important step for catalyzing further research in this area, as our artifacts can be a starting point for future studies."
  ]
}